        </apply>
        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <lev1>
                    <para>The Kysor fan clutch is spring-loaded ON or in the "engaged position" when the key is in the
                        OFF position.
                    </para>
                </lev1>
                <lev1>
                    <para>When the engine coolant temperature does not require the fan to operate, the fan control
                        system uses 90-120 psi air pressure to disengage the fan.
                    </para>
                </lev1>
                <lev1>
                    <para>The fan control system is integrated with the operation of shutters and air conditioning
                        systems if they are part of the vehicle.
                    </para>
                </lev1>
                <lev1>
                    <para>The basic control system shown in
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f1200101">Figure 1</hotlnk>consists of:
                    </para>
                </lev1>
                <lev1>
                    <figure id="f1200101" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="g1200101" filename="../figg12/G1200101.webp" type="webp"/>
                        <caption>Figure 1. Fan Clutch Components</caption>
                        <calloutgroup>
                            <callout1>1.THERMAL SWITCH (NORMALLY CLOSED)</callout1>
                            <callout1>2.SOLENOID VALVE (NORMALLY CLOSED)</callout1>
                            <callout1>3.FILTER</callout1>
                        </calloutgroup>
                    </figure>
                </lev1>
                <lev1>
                    <seqlist>
                        <item>
                            <para>A normally closed fan control Alarmstat or thermal switch that senses the engine
                                coolant temperature.
                            </para>
                        </item>
                        <item>
                            <para>Normally Closed solenoid valve (Normally Closed or NC means that with the key in the
                                OFF position the valve is closed) that receives voltage from the Alarmstat.
                            </para>
                        </item>
                        <item>
                            <para>An air operated Kysor Fan Clutch that is spring-loaded in the engaged position (fan
                                on).
                            </para>
                        </item>
                    </seqlist>
                </lev1>
            </geninfo>
        </description>
